# Bug Memory Log Rule

When a bug is solved, do not consider it complete until it is verified.

After verification, always update:
- `.local-ai-memory/bug-reference.md`

For each new bug entry, include:
- Symptom
- Root cause
- Fix applied (files/migrations/endpoints)
- Verification proof (tests or real-case check)
- Regression guard (test/checklist)

Rules:
- Add only confirmed solved bugs (not partial or unverified).
- Keep entries concise, actionable, and dated.
- If a bug is reopened, append an update to the same section with what changed.
- Do not store secrets or tokens in the bug reference file.
